<TITLE> HC orders protection of Gulshan-Banani-Baridhara lakes </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 14 (bdnews24.com) The court said any legitimate structure lying within the lake's boundaries would be relocated and the owners provided with compensation. The government and DCC may take criminal action against encroachers and seek compensation from them if appropriate, the court orders said. The bench of justices ABM Khairul Haque and Mohammad Momtaz Uddin Ahmed gave the orders on a petition by Gulshan Society executive secretary Kazi Mosharraf Hossain. The court also said the Department of Environment should ascertain whether environmental laws had been broken regarding the lake and directed the police to lend their support in the matter. The Department of Environment are to inform the court of its progress on this matter by Feb 15, 2010, said the High Court. b
